# Attaching and Accessing Message Metadata in useChat

## Server-Side: Sending Metadata

Define a metadata schema using Zod for type safety:

```tsx
export const messageMetadataSchema = z.object({
  createdAt: z.number().optional(),
  model: z.string().optional(),
  totalTokens: z.number().optional(),
});
```

In your API route, use the `messageMetadata` callback within `toUIMessageStreamResponse`:

```ts
return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse({
  originalMessages: messages,
  messageMetadata: ({ part }) => {
    if (part.type === 'start') {
      return {
        createdAt: Date.now(),
        model: 'your-model-id',
      };
    }
    if (part.type === 'finish') {
      return {
        totalTokens: part.totalUsage.totalTokens,
      };
    }
  },
});
```

## Client-Side: Accessing Metadata

Access metadata through the `message.metadata` property in your component:

```tsx
const { messages } = useChat<MyUIMessage>();

return (
  <div>
    {messages.map(message => (
      <div key={message.id}>
        {message.metadata?.createdAt && (
          <span>{new Date(message.metadata.createdAt)
            .toLocaleTimeString()}</span>
        )}
        {message.metadata?.totalTokens && (
          <div>{message.metadata.totalTokens} tokens</div>
        )}
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
);
```

Pass `originalMessages` typed to your custom message type to enable type-safe metadata handling.

